SIMPLE: intolerant
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intolerant
<hw>In*tol"er*ant</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n*t⟦ocr⟧l"⟦etil⟧r*⟦ait⟧nt)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>intolerans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>intol⟦eacute⟧rant</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Tolerant</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not enduring; not able to endure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The powers of human bodies being limited and <qex>intolerant</qex>
of excesses.</q> <rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not tolerating difference of opinion or sentiment,
especially in religious matters; refusing to allow others the enjoyment
of their opinions, rights, or worship; unjustly impatient of the opinion
of those disagree with us; not tolerant; unforbearing;
bigoted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Religion, harsh, <qex>intolerant</qex>, austere,⟦br⟧
Parent of manners like herself severe.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intolerant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Intolerant
<hw>In*tol"er*ant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An intolerant person; a
bigot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intolerantly</ent>⟦br⟧
